(152, 1, '2019-05-19 10:11:56', '2019-05-19 10:11:56', '<h2>SUPPLY, DEMAND AND VALUE CHAINS</h2>\r\nSupply Chain Management is the management of the flow of products and information from producer to end consumer, both inter &amp; intra organizational, and the management of all tangible and intangible assets employed whereas Demand Chain Management is the management of consumer demand and the subsequent flow of information &amp; products to and from end consumers through the various distribution channels and the management of all tangible and intangible assets employed. DCM is a chain of activities through which the supplier recognizes customer demand.\r\n<h2>Purpose &amp; Goal of SCM &amp; DCM:</h2>\r\nSCM is a business support function that is essentially operational in nature with the goal of providing high customer value through optimization with an appropriate level of resources to create a competitive advantage. A primary objective of SCM is the creation of value and in so doing, increase the profitability of the entire network of users, and fulfill predictable demand at the lowest possible cost. While DCM is a business support function that is essentially demand driven in nature with a goal of providing high customer value through customization with the least level of resources to create with competitive advantages.', 'SUPPLY, DEMAND AND VALUE CHAINS', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'supply-demand-and-value-chains', '', '', '2019-05-19 10:20:05', '2019-05-19 10:20:05', '', 0, 'http://localhost/underscore_2019/?p=152', 0, 'post', '', 0),
