(189, 1, '2019-05-19 10:44:07', '2019-05-19 10:44:07', '<h1>G7._Full_overview</h1>\r\nThe G7 concept of Business English has been divided into 4 parts. They are as following:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The G7 Concept</li>\r\n 	<li>The G7 method is special</li>\r\n 	<li>The G7 model of Business English</li>\r\n 	<li>The G7 typical proposal</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<em><strong>Part 1: The G7 Concept:</strong></em>\r\nThis part describes Business English, Performance Training, and Communication Skills. G7 helps businesses make more profits and grow faster through performance-based consulting, coaching and training. We start by working with clients to understand their business and their needs\r\n What is their strategy?\r\n What are they trying to achieve?\r\n How can we help them?\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Part 1: The G7 method is special:</strong></em>G7 and TBC were created by Jon Scott and Ian Kirkwood based on research undertaken on Korean students of Business English. Ian and Jon believe that Asian students need a much better form of education if they are to be effective communicators in global business in the 21st Century. TBC is 100 percent unique. No-one else can offer the same programs or the same long-lasting benefits. All materials and workbooks used by G7 have been personally written and created by Ian and Jon.\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Part 1: The G7 model of Business English:</strong></em>This part is divided in mainly three parts. They are General Business Communications (GBC), Specific Business Communications (SBC), Performance Business Communications (PBC).\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Part 1: The G7 typical proposal:</strong></em>Intensive Business Program (IBP)\r\nObjectives  What do we want to achieve?\r\nCurriculum  How will we achieve it?\r\nSyllabus  What are the programme specifics?\r\nMeasure  How will achievement be measured?', 'G7._Full_overview', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'g7-_full_overview', '', '', '2019-05-19 10:44:07', '2019-05-19 10:44:07', '', 0, 'http://localhost/underscore_2019/?p=189', 0, 'post', '', 0),
