(195, 1, '2019-05-19 10:55:58', '2019-05-19 10:55:58', '<h1>Business Etiquette, CCC</h1>\r\nBusiness Etiquette focuses on two key points:\r\n1. Cultivating social skills\r\n2. Developing cultural understanding\r\nThis helps to leverage business communications between people of Eastern, Western, and Western cultures.\r\n\r\nBusiness Etiquette are divided in six parts.\r\n\r\n<em>Part 1: An Introduction to the World of Global Business Etiquette</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Part 2: Breaking Down Society by 4 factors  Power Distance, Uncertainty Avoidance, Masculinity/ Femininity and Individualism/ collectivism.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Part 3: Combination Comparisons  Power Distance &amp; Collectivism, Power Distance &amp; Uncertainty Avoidance, Collectivism &amp; Masculinity, Collectivism &amp; Uncertainty Avoidance</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Part 4: Which Countries are the Easiest and Hardest to do Business with  due to differences in Cultural Behaviors</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Part 5: Possible solutions that both Westerners and Easterners can use in order to increase Business Etiquette Skills</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Part 6: Understanding the differences in High and Low Context societies and what is expected from people operating within these systems.</em>', 'Business Etiquette, CCC', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'business-etiquette-ccc', '', '', '2019-05-19 10:55:58', '2019-05-19 10:55:58', '', 0, 'http://localhost/underscore_2019/?p=195', 0, 'post', '', 0),
